# Makefile.local.example — per-host Make overrides for the e2e suite.
#
# Copy to `Makefile.local` (git-ignored) and edit for your environment. The
# Makefile `-include`s it, so these win over the tracked defaults; anything you
# pass on the `make` command line still wins over both.
#
# Most setups need NOTHING here: with a local Postgres and a host `psql`, plain
# `make test-e2e` resets the e2e DB over E2E_DATABASE_URL on its own. Fill this in
# only when your e2e database is behind a container or a nonstandard port.

# Where the disposable e2e database lives (NOT your dev DB — the suite wipes it).
# E2E_DATABASE_URL := postgres://chat:chat_dev_pw@localhost:55432/chat_e2e?sslmode=disable

# How the pre-run schema wipe reaches Postgres when there's no usable host `psql`
# (e.g. it runs inside the container that hosts the DB). global-setup.js exports
# the wipe SQL to this command as $E2E_RESET_SQL — keep the literal, unexpanded
# "$E2E_RESET_SQL" here (the recipe passes it through for the shell to expand).
# Replace <pg-container> with your container's name.
# E2E_DB_RESET_CMD := podman exec -i -e PGPASSWORD=chat_dev_pw <pg-container> psql -U chat -d chat_e2e -v ON_ERROR_STOP=1 -c "$$E2E_RESET_SQL"

# Opt in to the Firefox (Gecko-engine) smoke project. Gecko needs no native host
# stack on Linux, so just set the flag — the browser bundle is fetched on first
# `make test-e2e`. (The WebKit smoke is heavier: it needs a provisioned native
# stack and a setup hook — see docs/testing/cross-browser.md.)
# E2E_FIREFOX := 1
